metadata.name: Totalistic Cellular Automata #468
metadata.description:
Totalistic Cellular Automata is a work celebrating my appreciation and love for 1D Cellular Automata. In this piece there are many different rules and rulesets which dictate how the cells will behave. Totalistic cellular automata is a type of cellular automata where the total or average values of cells in a neighborhood are what the rules depend on.

Clicking the image continues or pauses the generation.

There are 4 dimension sizes, 4 possible states, 52 possible rulesets, and 55 colorways. 

This generator was inspired by the works and discoveries of Stephen Wolfram and ‚ÄúRGB Elementary Cellular Automata‚Äù by Ciphrd which will always have a special place in my heart.

JohnWow(2022)

metadata.name: Last Lines #97
metadata.description:
How many lines have been drawn on fxhash since that first generative logo started growing on a Wednesday in early November? How many brush strokes, wires, cables, threads? Many thousands per mint? Millions per project? Billions in total? Shall we add just a few more to celebrate the end of the genesis? Here are 222 iterations with 111 lines each. Each line connects two edges of the canvas but may get deflected by hidden attractors in an attempt to minimize friction and deviation from its path.

Press [p]rint to save a high resolution capture.

This artwork is fully generative and was entirely hand-coded in 4,400 characters of plain JavaScript. Forever limited to 222 editions on the Tezos blockchain. I hope you will enjoy yours. London, March 2022.

metadata.name: The Valley ‚Ä¢ Landscape study #32
metadata.description:
Code-generated landscapes inspired by the valley I live in.

This study focuses on building harmonious color palettes, grainy textures and bringing back the feeling of contemplating vast landscapes. Textures are inspired by vintage travel posters from early 20th century.

Main features :
- Random aspect ratio : from 0.67:1 (portrait) to 3:1 (panoramic) with any variation in between
- 11 color palettes : 8 for day time (2 by season), 3 for night time ("Quiet Moon", "Golden Moon", and "Blood Moon")

Press [S] to save as PNG

metadata.name: Phantoms #249
metadata.description:
Phantoms is a series of hazy memories of distant places. Some tranquil, others sinister, each scene is as much defined by what is revealed as by what remains unseen.

In this collection I aim to juxtapose hard and soft. Blocky shapes form the core of the compositions. Upon these surfaces, soft textures appear to flow and drip over the sides. Varying levels of opacity, lighting, and fog effects further soften the scenes to create an atmospheric, dream-like quality. By remaining semi-abstract, each of the color palettes are given the space to influence the mood dramatically.

metadata.name: Sherwood #52
metadata.description:
In the forest, foggy, cloudy weather creates a mysterious, otherworldly atmosphere.

----

Controls:
s or [double click] - save
1 through 8 - set the pixel density for higher resolutions. Base is 2000x1000.
d - increase debug level (none, overlay, overlay + animated drawing)
D - decrease debug level
[plus] or [equal] - increase the edition of the mint (see a new location with the same features)
[minus] - decrease the edition, to a minimum of zero

Made with:
- p5js
- Simplex noise (hills, cleared/forested, grass height, tree size & separation)
- Poisson disk sampling (tree distribution)
